Treasury Sanctions Sinaloa Cartel Lieutenant
Misunderstandings and disagreements can be fertile ground for creating something new. That’s why it can be useful for CFOs to foster the right kind of friction between workgroup members. When people are willing and able to challenge each other’s ideas and assumptions they can think about problems and solutions in ways that each member would not likely get to on their own. Learn how to cultivate productive friction in the service of developing new solutions to challenging problems.